---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../../consts';

const faq = [
  { q: 'How do you start A Bridge Too Far in Moonlight Peaks?', a: 'Confirmed: it follows "Orlock\u2019s Wine Scheme" — apologize to Orlock, pay Samael a 350-gold debt at The Broken Lamp, then report back to Orlock. A cutscene then triggers on entering town, showing Orlock, Evan, and Mina locked out of the Ambrosia Estate.' },
  { q: 'Why is the bridge to Misty Shores blocked?', a: 'Player-reported/community-sourced: Orlock believes Fiona hexed the bridge out of spite. It turns out there was no actual curse — the two had a falling-out where Orlock said something rude, and the "curse" is really just the fallout from that argument.' },
  { q: 'What do you need to do to fix the bridge?', a: 'Community-reported: speak to each of the requested spellcasters (Fiona, Sabrina, Luna, and Noel are named in coverage) and then return to the bridge. After a short cutscene, the curse lifts and the area opens.' },
  { q: 'What does A Bridge Too Far unlock?', a: 'Confirmed: completing it reopens the Ambrosia Estate and unlocks Misty Shores, including the Cave of Echoes — your source of Copper Ore for tool upgrades.' },
];

const jsonLd = [
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Quests', item: new URL('/quests', SITE.url).href },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: 'A Bridge Too Far', item: new URL('/quests/a-bridge-too-far', SITE.url).href },
  ] },
];
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks: A Bridge Too Far Quest Guide"
  description="How to start and finish A Bridge Too Far in Moonlight Peaks: the Orlock/Fiona bridge feud, who to talk to, and what it unlocks (Misty Shores, Cave of Echoes, copper)."
  path="/quests/a-bridge-too-far"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Quests', href: '/quests' }, { label: 'A Bridge Too Far' }]}
  showExport
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Quest guide</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks: <em>A Bridge Too Far</em></h1>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Quick answer:</strong> A Bridge Too Far unlocks after "Orlock's Wine Scheme." Talk to
        the town's spellcasters (Fiona, Sabrina, Luna, and Noel are named in early walkthroughs), then
        return to the bridge outside the Ambrosia Estate. Finishing it opens Misty Shores and the Cave
        of Echoes — your first source of Copper Ore.
      </div>

      <h2>How to start A Bridge Too Far</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed: this quest follows directly from <strong>Orlock's Wine Scheme</strong>, the
        opening quest where Orlock asks you to make him Blood Wine. That quest resolves with you
        apologizing to Orlock, paying off a 350-gold debt to Samael at The Broken Lamp, and reporting
        back. A Bridge Too Far then triggers automatically the next time you walk into town, with a
        cutscene showing Orlock, Evan, and Mina locked out of the Ambrosia Estate.
      </p>

      <h2>Prerequisite quests</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/characters/orlock">Orlock's Wine Scheme</a> — make Blood Wine, resolve the Samael debt.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why the bridge is blocked</h2>
      <p>
        <span class="tag-community">Community-reported</span> Orlock believes Fiona cursed the
        bridge connecting the Ambrosia Estate to town, out of spite. The twist reported by early
        players: there's no real curse. Orlock and Fiona had an argument in which Orlock said
        something rude, and the "hex" is really just fallout from that falling-out — the quest is
        as much about patching up a family feud as it is a literal magical fix.
      </p>

      <h2>Step-by-step progression</h2>
      <p><span class="tag-community">Community-reported</span> — not independently re-verified by us step for step, but consistent across multiple launch-week walkthroughs:</p>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Finish "Orlock's Wine Scheme" (apologize to Orlock, pay Samael 350 gold, report back).</li>
        <li>Enter town to trigger the cutscene revealing the Ambrosia Estate lockout.</li>
        <li>Talk to <a href="/characters/fiona">Fiona</a>, <a href="/characters/sabrina">Sabrina</a>, <a href="/characters/luna">Luna</a>, and <a href="/characters/noel">Noel</a> — the witches/spellcasters named in coverage of this quest.</li>
        <li>Return to the bridge near the Ambrosia Estate once you've spoken to all of them.</li>
        <li>Watch the resolution cutscene — the curse lifts and the bridge opens.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>What the quest unlocks</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed: finishing A Bridge Too Far reopens the <strong>Ambrosia Estate</strong> and
        unlocks the wider <strong>Misty Shores</strong> area, including the <strong>Cave of
        Echoes</strong> — the mine in the lower-left of Misty Shores where you find Copper Ore.
      </p>

      <h2>Relationship to Misty Shores</h2>
      <p>
        Misty Shores stays gated until this quest resolves. If you're blocked on fishing, mining, or
        other Misty Shores content, this quest — not a missing shop item — is almost always the
        actual bottleneck.
      </p>

      <h2>Relationship to the Cave of Echoes</h2>
      <p>
        <span class="tag-community">Community-reported</span> Once the bridge opens, head to the far
        left corner of the beach and enter the hole in the cliffside to reach the Cave of Echoes.
        Copper Ore looks like ordinary rock with copper flecks; break it with a Pickaxe. Large ore
        clusters can drop up to 6 ore versus 1 from regular nodes. Make a Copper Bar at the Furnace
        with 4 Copper Ore + 1 Charcoal.
      </p>

      <h2>Relationship to finding Death</h2>
      <p>
        The Ambrosia Graveyard, where Death can be found, sits near the Ambrosia Mansion in the same
        area this quest reopens — so if you can't find Death yet, finishing this quest is a likely
        prerequisite. See the Death profile page for what's separately confirmed about him.
      </p>

      <h2>Common problems</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Quest won't trigger:</strong> confirm you've actually finished Orlock's Wine
          Scheme (paid Samael and reported back to Orlock), not just started it.</li>
        <li><strong>Can't find one of the spellcasters:</strong> Fiona and Noel are both in Moonlit
          Pines; Sabrina and Luna are usually found in or near their shops in town.</li>
        <li><strong>Bridge still blocked after talking to everyone:</strong> not yet confirmed here
          — if you've spoken to all four and it's still stuck, this may be an ordering issue or a
          bug; check <a href="/known-issues">known issues</a> or report it via the feedback thumbs-down.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        {faq.map((f) => (
          <details>
            <summary>{f.q}</summary>
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Related: <a href="/quests">all quests</a>, <a href="/locations/mines">Cave of Echoes & mines</a>,
        <a href="/characters/death">Death</a>, <a href="/characters/orlock">Orlock</a>,
        <a href="/characters/fiona">Fiona</a>.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  <style>
    .tag-community {
      display: inline-block; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      color: var(--faint); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 999px; padding: 2px 8px;
      margin-right: 6px; vertical-align: middle;
    }
  </style>
</Base>
